    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-04-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="669"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d669">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79620 Boeing Airplane Co./29</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boding</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1928</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received May 23.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1076</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to the Department’s
                    instruction No. 574, dated February 9, 1928,<note n="8" xml:id="d669fn8">See
                        footnote 99, <ref target="#pg_821">p. 821</ref>.</note> instructing the
                    Legation to request the Ecuadorean authorities to grant Mr. Ralph A. O’Neill
                    permission to fly in Ecuador, in the interest of the Boeing Airplane Company and
                    the Pratt and Whitney Motor Corporation, and to enclose, herewith, a copy and
                    translation of the reply of the Ecuadorean Ministry for Foreign Relations<note
                        n="9" xml:id="d669fn9">Not printed.</note> to the Legation’s informal note
                    sent in compliance with the Department’s instruction.</p>
                <p>It will be noted that the request to fly in Ecuador is granted and that orders
                    extending all possible facilities to Captain O’Neill will be issued.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">G. A. Bading</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
